  "name": "Parkinson's Disease - Medication Query (Levodopa)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find Parkinson's patients via levodopa prescriptions. Levodopa is the cornerstone PD therapy and is highly disease-specific.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed levodopa for Parkinson's disease.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on Parkinson's medications.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed levodopa — the foundational dopamine precursor therapy for Parkinson's disease.",
    "expert": "Identify patients on levodopa therapy by searching MedicationRequest resources for levodopa prescriptions coded in RxNorm. Levodopa is the cornerstone treatment for Parkinson's disease and is highly disease-specific relative to most neurological medications; however, it is occasionally used for restless legs syndrome or atypical parkinsonism, so a levodopa-only cohort will include a small proportion of non-PD patients representing the cross-indication population."
  },
